article.headline: E. Michigan 65, Manhattan 51
article.story: YPSILANTI, Mich. (AP) -- Brandon Bowdry scored 14 points and Jesse Bunkley added 12 Saturday to lead Eastern Michigan to a 65-51 victory over Manhattan in a BracketBuster game. Justin Dobbins also had 10 points for the Eagles (10-16), who have won two of their past three games. Devon Austin had 16 points and Darryl Crawford and Jamel Ferguson each added 10 for the Jaspers (12-15), who lost their fourth in a row. Leading by four points at halftime, Eastern Michigan broke the game open by scoring 17 of the first 24 points of the second half. Bowdry had seven points during the run. The Eagles did not allow Manhattan any closer than 12 points over the final 10 minutes. Eastern Michigan increased its lead to as much as 19 points and held the Jaspers to just 12 of 36 shooting from the field in the second half. The 51 points equaled the fewest points scored against the Eagles this season. Both teams played a sloppy first half, combining for 22 turnovers. There were two lead changes and two ties before Eastern Michigan scored the final four points to take a 27-23 halftime lead.
